{"questionId":"30439054","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 (using values from part (a))</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to use sine rule with their values from part (a) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mi>b</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mi>a</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>correct working that leads to <em><strong>AG</strong></em> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 (double-angle identity)<br></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>using double-angle identity &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>correct working (involving substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>) that leads to <em><strong>AG&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30439054","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that b=3a4.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}